time required: 20 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

Drain and rinse @chickpeas{13.4%oz can}; dry thoroughly with #paper towels{}. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp}, @shawarma spice blend{1%tbsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and crisp, ~{18-20%minutes}.

> TIP: It's natural for chickpeas to pop a bit while roasting.

While chickpeas roast, wash and dry all produce.

Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz}. Trim and halve @Persian cucumber{1} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. Pick and roughly chop fronds from @dill{1/4%oz}.

In a #large bowl{}, toss together tomatoes, cucumber, chopped dill, @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Toast @whole wheat pitas{2} until warm and pliable. Halve each pita crosswise to create pockets.

Spread @hummus{4%tbsp} and @sour cream{6%tbsp} inside of each pita pocket. Fill with as many chickpeas as you like (you may have some left over) and a small amount of salad.

Divide stuffed pita pockets between plates. Serve with remaining salad on the side.

> TIP: Sprinkle your salad with any remaining chickpeas for a crunchy, crouton-like topper!